      {
        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Chemistry Insight\nAmino acids are among the most data-rich ligand classes in SRD-46 — their bifunctional α-amino/α-carboxylate backbone forms stable 5-membered chelate rings with virtually all transition and main-group metals. The 297 entries span simple aliphatic amino acids (glycine, alanine) all the way to complex side-chain donors (histidine, cysteine, EDTA-like derivatives), making this class central to bioinorganic and environmental coordination chemistry.\n\n> **Source:** NIST SRD-46 database",
